104
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:18,079
Running the chase.

105
00:05:18,079 --> 00:05:22,479
Participants in the chase are strongly motivated to use the dash action every round,

106
00:05:22,479 --> 00:05:28,479
which you use your action, which you would normally take to attack or cast a magic spell

107
00:05:28,479 --> 00:05:31,919
to move double your speed during the chase.

108
00:05:33,759 --> 00:05:38,319
And then pursuers who stop to cast spells and make attacks run the risk of losing their quarry.

109
00:05:38,319 --> 00:05:42,560
So you can run 30 feet, but if you cast a spell, they may bolt ahead on their next turn,

110
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,639
which means you can't exactly catch them.

111
00:05:44,639 --> 00:05:49,039
During the chase, a participant can freely use the dash action a number of times equal to

112
00:05:49,039 --> 00:05:51,360
three plus your constitution modifier.

113
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:57,519
Each additional dash action it takes during the chase requires the creature to succeed

114
00:05:57,519 --> 00:06:03,120
a DC 10 constitution check at the end of its turn or gain one level of exhaustion.

115
00:06:04,079 --> 00:06:07,360
The participant drops out if they reach level five.

116
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:11,919
Since its speed becomes zero, you can also die.

117
00:06:11,919 --> 00:06:12,560
Don't do that.

118
00:06:13,439 --> 00:06:18,000
A creature can remove levels of exhaustion it gained during the chase by finishing a

119
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,199
short or long rest, which we're not going to really worry about right now.

120
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:25,680
So you have free reign of dash until you use up your number?

121
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:26,160
Yeah.

122
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,360
And then you have to roll for it?

123
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:30,959
So if you have four, once you hit four, you're donezo.

124
00:06:33,439 --> 00:06:34,079
Spells and attacks.

125
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:38,399
A chase participant can make an attack or cast a spell against other creatures within range.

126
00:06:38,399 --> 00:06:41,279
Apply the normal rules for cover terrain and all that stuff.

127
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:45,680
Chase participants can't normally make opportunity attacks against each other since

128
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:48,080
they all are assumed to be moving in the same direction.

129
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:53,840
So if you catch up to them and they move out of range, just based on how initiative works,

130
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:58,160
you can't then swipe at them the same way opportunity attacks would work.

131
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,280
Ending a chase if one side stops.

132
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,120
That ends the chase.

133
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:09,280
If neither side gives up, the quarry makes a stealth check at the end of each round

134
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:12,080
after every participant in the chase has taken its turn.

135
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,880
The result is compared to the passive wisdom perception.

136
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:20,240
So if they make a stealth check and nobody sees them disappear, you lose them.

137
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:24,800
